article.description: — Cameron Krutwig had 22 points as Loyola of Chicago easily beat Chicago State 88-51 on Wednesday.
article.headline: Krutwig leads Loyola of Chicago past Chicago State 88-51
article.linkText: Krutwig leads Loyola of Chicago past Chicago State 88-51
article.story: CHICAGO -- — Cameron Krutwig had 22 points as Loyola of Chicago easily beat Chicago State 88-51 on Wednesday. Krutwig made 10 of 13 shots and grabbed nine rebounds. Tate Hall had 15 points for Loyola of Chicago (2-0). Marquise Kennedy added six assists. Levelle Zeigler had 12 points for the Cougars (0-6). Ke'Sean Davis added 10 points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
